cs.AI, cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.CR, cs.SE 

This paper deals with the problem of reasoning and planning with incomplete knowledge, which is a core topic in artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.AI is the most likely sub-category. The paper also introduces a knowledge representation scheme called PSIPLAN, which is related to logic and ontology, making cs.LO a likely sub-category as well. The paper also presents a procedure for state update resulting from taking an action in PSIPLAN, which is related to planning and control, making cs.PL a likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the soundness and completeness of the entailment in PSIPLAN, which is related to cryptography and security, making cs.CR a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions the implementation of PSIPLAN in Common Lisp and its use in an application on planning in a collaborative interface, which is related to software engineering, making cs.SE a possible sub-category.
